<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/982> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #982" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Pro praetore (Liv. 10.26.15, and 30.1). Marched on Clusium and drew Etruscan forces away from Sentinum (10.27.5-6, and 30.1-2; cf. also Frontin. Str. 2.5.9)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/959> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #959" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 10.11.10; Act. Tr. (on Fulvius); Chr. 354 (Scipione et Centumalo) Fast. Hyd. (Scipione et Maximo), so also Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; Degrassi 38f., 111, 424f. According to Livy, Scipio won a victory in Etruria (10.12.3-8), but according to the Elogium (CIL 1\n     , 2.7; ILS 1) he captured Taurasia and Cisauna of Samnium and subdued Lucania.\n     \n      1\n     \n     According to Act. Tr., Fulvius was victorious in Etruria and Samnium but Livy (10.12.3 and 9, and 13.1) records only that he took Bovianum and Aufidena of Samnium, and celebrated a triumph (Degrassi 72f., 543). Frontinus (Str. 1.6.1-2, and 11.2) takes him to Lucania." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/944> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #944" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under the Dictator Valerius against the Etruscans (Liv. 10.4.8-12, cf. 5.5)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1122> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1122" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., clavi figendi causa; Degrassi, 40f., 115, 432f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10096> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10096" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Samnitibus, Etrusceisque. MRR I.174, Itgenshorst no. 91, Rich no. 91." .
